ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class AnswerCall

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.AnswerCall
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AnswerCall
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Answers a call that is ringing, queued, or being offered to a device. This service is typically associated with devices that have attached speakerphone units and headset telephones to connect to a call via hands-free operation. For example, when the call is answered, one of the following actions may occur:
    • If the specified device has a speaker and a microphone, the speaker and microphone are turned on.
    • If the specified device only has a speaker, the speaker is turned on. The handset must be picked up in order to have a two way conversation.
    • If there is no speaker, then the handset must be picked up in order to have a two-way conversation.
    • If the specified device has a headset, the headset is turned on.

    The AnswerCall request has these parameters:

    AnswerCall Request Parameters
    callToBeAnswered Mandatory Alerting connection to be answered

    CSTA Functional Requirements:

    1. If the computing function wants to clear an active call prior to answering an alerting or queued call for a device, it must first issue a ClearConnection service for the active call and then issue the Answer Call service for the alerting or queued call.

    Negative Acknowledgements:

    • stateIncompatibility:invalidCalledDeviceState - Sent if the station user did not go off-hook within five seconds and is not capable of being forced off-hook.
    • systemResourceAvailability:generic - Sent if the client attempted to add a seventh party to a call with six active participants.
    • operation:invalidConnectionID - Sent if an invalid connection ID specified.
    • operation:InvalidDeviceID - Sent if an invalid device ID is specified in callToBeAnswered
    • stateIncompatibility:invalidConnectionState - Sent if the specified connection is not in a valid state for this operation.
    • stateIncompatibility:noCallToAnswer - Sent if the call has been redirected to coverage.
    • systemResourceAvailability:ResourceBusy - Sent if the user is busy or there is no idle appearance available.
    • operation:securityViolation - Sent if the user was not authorized to control the specified device.
    • operation:generic - Sent if a logic error occurred in the code.
    • unspecified - Sent if an implementation specific error occurred.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
